previous_with_titles.title: Introduction
previous_with_titles.text: Hey guys, I'm Dina from simplyhomecooked.com and today I'll be showing you how to make these fluffy and moist blueberry muffins.

previous_with_titles.title: Fill Muffin Cups
previous_with_titles.text: Divide the batter among the 12 muffin cups, filling each about 2/3 of the way full. Try to divide the batter evenly.

previous_with_titles.title: Rest Batter
previous_with_titles.text: Let the muffin batter rest for about 15 minutes before baking, or rest between cooking different batches if making a larger batch.

previous_with_titles.title: Bake Muffins
previous_with_titles.text: Bake in the 425-degree oven for 7 minutes. Then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees without opening the oven door and continue baking for 12-15 minutes.

last_step.title: Step 9: Add Melted Butter
last_step.text: Continue beating with your electric mixer as you slowly gradually add in four tablespoons of melted unsalted butter.
